   <p><placeName ref="cwgk:P00002906">E. Town</placeName> <date when="1861-02-22">Feby 22. 1861</date>
    <lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N001002">G W Johnson Esqr</persName>
<lb/>my dear Sir</p>
<p>I receive your letter this moment. Would have written you sooner had the promise of Eight Thousand Dollars. <unclear>Very</unclear> shortly. when pd. shall be pd on your debt-</p>
<p>I fear I shall not get any think from the south for some time, Should things take a change I will <unclear/> <unclear/> of the debt thair- rest ashured my dear Sir that every effort on my part shall be, to pay you the ballance at as early day as possable.</p>
<p>I will advise you when I pay the 8000$ on the note</p>
<p>Truly your-
<lb/>friend
 <lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00008144">S B Thomas</persName><pb/></p>
<p>S. B. Thomas
